Check out our live tasting! Chris & Kim taste this week's specialty can & coffee releases, which will all be released this Thursday, July 15th at 9am online. They also show off on our Pure Pride eco-Shirts available now online and in taprooms! All shirt proceeds go to @bravetrails !

MURKWOOD
Murky IPA with Nelson Sauvin & Pacifica Hops
7% ABV

CATACLYSMIC EVENT
Murky Quintuple IPA with Nelson Sauvin, Riwaka, & Citra Cryo Hops
15% ABV

NIGHT ON GHOST MOUNTAIN BARREL-AGED ETHIOPIA GUJI
*Collaboration with @mostracoffee & @lostcausemeadery

All specialty releases will be available for purchase online starting Thursday, July 15th at 9am.

*IMPORTANT: The sale starts at 9am PST on Thursday, July 15th. We anticipate this to be a high-demand sale with a limited number of cans. We recommend being prepared to initiate your purchase right at 9am PST. As always, we appreciate your interest in our beer, and your support and understanding of our efforts as a small boutique brewery.

Details at link in profile.

Join in as Devin Tastes this Week's Special Release, DDH UNITED, & Announces Raffle Winners with Special Guests Lexus and Eh Ler from @outdooroutreach !

DDH United returns in time to secure your cans for the 4th of July! Available for purchase this Thursday, June 17th online at 9am!

DDH United
Double Dry Hopped Murky IPA with Citra & Mosaic Hops
6.9% ABV

A tribute to the American hop, this complex murky IPA features hand-selected Citra and Mosaic hops from Washington which accentuate the fruity esters of our murky yeast strain. We double dry hopped this beauty to give it a super juicy boost, adding notes of mango, pineapple, tangerine, and lychee in both aroma and flavor. 

RAFFLE: Congrats to the lucky winners and thanks to everyone who participated in the raffle supporting @outdooroutreach !

node.text:
We are proud to source our organic strawberries locally from @jrorganicsfarm. Located just up the road in North County, J.R. Organics is a fourth generation family farm that is California Certified Organic Farmers (CCOF) certified. All of their produce is grown in the purest way possible...including the 10,000 pounds of strawberries that are being added to our strawberry brews this season!

We believe every beer should tell a story. As we celebrate our fifth year in partnership with J.R. Organics, we took our team to the farm to taste the strawberries, check out the fields where they were grown, and get to know the family that grew them. From our brewers to our beertenders, everyone had the opportunity for a hands-on experience to connect with the ingredients. Because of this experience, we can convey the rich story behind the beer—the organic farm, the multi-generational family, the sweetest San Diego strawberries—and enrich your experience when you taste it in your glass.

Learn more at the Strawberry Fest link in our profile.

#pureproject #strawberryfest #jrorganics #organic #strawberries #sdbeer

Strawberry season is upon us and we’re excited to release your favorite strawberry beers again this year, brewed with local organic strawberries from J.R. Organics. Today Chris and Cheyna taste and discuss the first in our Strawberry Fest 2021 lineup, Sunset Crush!

SUNSET CRUSH
Cream Ale with Strawberry & Vanilla
5.8% ABV

A summer twist on our house cream ale, Sunset Crush is full of fruity, bright acidity thanks to 1500 pounds of local, organic strawberries from J.R. Organics. The addition of organic Tahitian vanilla bean creates a sweet and creamy backbone to showcase the strawberries—a true reflection of our local terroir. This refreshing ale got its name for a reason—it is the perfect beer to crush while basking in the beauty of a San Diego sunset.

Sunset Crush will be released on draft at all taprooms on Thursday, May 27th. Come for a fresh pour, or take a fill home with you.

Make sure to follow along as we continue the Strawberry Fest 2021 releases!

#pureproject #strawberryfest #jrorganics #organic #strawberries #sdbeer

The ladies of Pure proudly present Pure Passion, a pale ale brewed for International Women's Collaboration Brew Day.

PURE PASSION
*International Women's Collaboration Brew Day
Pale Ale with Strata, Simcoe, & Motueka Hops
5.5% ABV

Donning an unfiltered straw color and lacy white head, this medium-bodied creation is hopped with Strata, Simcoe, and Motueka. The result is a vibrant lime zest on the nose that transforms to grapefruit on the palate. Complementary essences of peach, guava, pineapple and pine convey the pure passion that the ladies put into this one.

Join us at any of our taprooms for a fresh pour, or take a crowler or growler home with you. We look forward to seeing you!

Fresh on tap now at all locations!

NOMAD
Hefeweizen
5.7% ABV

Inspired by the traditional German-style hefeweizen—a summertime specialty in Bavaria—our hefeweizen, Nomad, makes its long-awaited return. Its murky pale appearance comes from a mixed malt bill including Admiral Pils, unmalted wheat from Durst Family Farms, malted white wheat, and a touch of oats. Its classic fruity ester essences are thanks to the traditional Bavarian Weizen yeast strain, and its subtle spice from the Noble hop. Expect aromas of lemon cake and banana pudding, and a world of flavors including pear, wheat, clove, subtle banana and black pepper. But thirsty wanderers be warned—its dry finish will leave your palate craving more.

Come for a fresh pint. Miramar, @purebalboapark and @purecarlsbad are open 12-10pm today, and @purebrewingvista is open 3-9pm. See you soon!

Roes Red is our fresh take on a Flanders red ale, and a Great American Beer Fest medal winner at that! Flanders red ales have their origins in Belgium, dating back hundreds of years. We have blended this Belgian tradition with another adopted from the sherry producers on the Iberian Peninsula, the solera brewing method. Our new-world approach to both the solera system and Flanders styles of old, along with the addition of Pure’s proprietary yeast blend, means our Roes Red has a fascinating history and a delicious future.

Learn more about what makes Roes Red so unique at the Education link in our profile!

Specialty can release TODAY—available for pickup at all taproom locations and for CA & NV shipping!

ZIGSA
Murky IPA with Nelson Sauvin, Citra, Cashmere, & Amarillo Hops
6.3% ABV

We are excited to reveal a beautiful new murky creation, Zigsa. This murky IPA was dry hopped with Nelson Sauvin, Citra, Cashmere, and Amarillo hops, creating aromas of pineapple, honeydew, mango and lychee that really jump out relative to the softness of the flavor. The palate showcases the nuances of the malt—particularly floral characteristics from the wheat—as well as essences of tangelo and cantaloupe. Zigsa is incredibly well balanced and this initial batch is as rare as its Tibetan snow leopard namesake; be sure to pick up a 4-pack while it's in sight. 

FOREST GUARDIAN
Murky Triple IPA with Strata, Mosaic, Pacific Jade, & Hallertau Blanc Hops
9.5% ABV

We proudly present Forest Guardian, a murky triple IPA that will stand up to the biggest of beasts. Much of its flavorful force is derived from a global medley of hops including Strata (Oregon), Mosaic (Washington), Pacific Jade (New Zealand), and Hallertau Blanc (Germany). Aromas of ripe papaya, orange marmalade and dank emerge from its murky golden appearance, along with flavors of resin, cantaloupe and clementine. Don't let the smooth, medium body fool you—this triple packs a punch.

Order your specialty cans now at the Can Release link in our profile.
